<!--h2>8-Beat Advanced Tutorial</h2-->

<p>
The advanced tutorial currently focuses on how to make triplets in 8-Beat.
</p>

<p>
The following song has been written in standard sheet music form, and
translated into 8-Beat notation. It should serve as an example of how to
translate triplets into 8-Beat notation.
</p>

<h2>Blackmail the Universe by Megadeth</h2>

<img src="triplets.png" alt="Blackmail the Universe sheet music">

<code><pre class="code smaller-text"><span class="comment"># Song: Blackmail the Universe
# Artist: Megadeth
# Translated to 8-Beat by Jacob Lacey
# (Transposed up an octave to help audibility)</span>
tempo = 174 
F#3, 6; F#3, 6; F#3, 12; E3,  12; F#3, 12; G3, 12; A3,  12; G3,  12; F#3, 12; E3,  12
F#3, 6; F#3, 6; F#3, 12; E3,  12; F#3, 12; G3, 12; A3,  12; B3,  12; C4,  12; C#4, 12
F#3, 6; F#3, 6; F#3, 12; E3,  12; F#3, 12; G3, 12; A3,  12; G3,  12; F#3, 12; E3,  12
F#3, 6; F#3, 6; C4,  12; B3,  12; A3,  12; G3, 12; F#3, 12; E3,  12; F#3, 12; G3,  12
G#3, 6; G#3, 6; G#3, 12; F#3, 12; G#3, 12; A3, 12; B3,  12; A3,  12; G#,  12; F#,  12
G#3, 6; G#3, 6; G#3, 12; F#3, 12; G#3, 12; A3, 12; B3,  12; C#4, 12; D,   12; D#,  12
G#3, 6; G#3, 6; G#3, 12; F#3, 12; G#3, 12; A3, 12; B3,  12; A3,  12; G#,  12; F#,  12
G#3, 6; G#3, 6; R,    6; R,    2
A#3, 6; A#3, 6; A#3, 12; G#3, 12; A#3, 12; B3, 12; C#4, 12; B3,  12; A#, 12; G#, 12
A#3, 6; A#3, 6; A#3, 12; G#3, 12; A#3, 12; B3, 12; C#4, 12; D#4, 12; E4, 12; F4, 12
A#3, 6; A#3, 6; A#3, 12; G#3, 12; A#3, 12; B3, 12; C#4, 12; B3,  12; A#, 12; G#, 12
A#3, 6; A#3, 6; R,    6; R,    2
</pre></code>

<p>
For triplets, multiply the note's base by 3 and divide by 2. For example, if
you want to make eighth note triplets, 8*3 = 24, 24/2 = 12. If you want to
make quarter note triplets, 4*3 = 12, 12/2 = 6. Triplets work this way in
8-Beat because all note values are entered as their fraction of a whole note.
</p>

